free_txt: Cross-section data on tape.
Electron linear accelerator of CBNM,
beam energy     =  55 MeV, beam peak current = 1.4 A ,
burst frequency = 400 Hz , burst width       =  50 ns.
-Corrected for self screening, multiple scattering
and spontaneous fission background of 94-Pu-240,
the rest of the background is negligible(as determined
with "black resonance" technique) relative to the time
independent spontaneous fission background of Pu-240.
-No corrections made for resolution and doppler effects
nor for difference in NU-BAR and fission neutron
spectra between 94-Pu-240 and 94-Pu-239 because of
absence of data for 94-Pu-240.
Result shows a strong resonance grouping structure.
Liquid scintillator tank for fission
neutrons, four NE213 filled chambers forming a hollow
cylinder of
inner diameter = 16 cm, outer diameter = 38 cm,
inner length   = 18 cm, outer length   = 38 cm.
Viewed by four 48 AVP photo multipliers.
Each photomultiplier has a pulse shape discriminator
against gamma radiation, they are linked pair wise to
six coincidence circuits, (slow-fast),
see J.Nucl.Ener.,22 211,Fig.2 and Fig.1 of reference .
4096 channel analyser with a channel width of 40 ns.
B-F(3) counters at about 60 m from LINAC target
for neutron spectrum monitoring.
Electron linear accelerator of CBNM,
beam energy     =  55 MeV, beam peak current = 1.4 A ,
burst frequency = 400 Hz , burst width       =  50 ns.
Mercury cooled natural 92-U target of LINAC.
Neutron moderator is a 200 mm * 200 mm, 24 mm thick
polyethylene slab, mounted close to target, parallel
to the electron beam.
Neutron spectrum proportional to (Energy)**(-0.887),
cut-off filter 5-B-10.
Time of flight, path length = 30.57 m.
Flight path at -9 degrees with the line perpendicular
to the polyethylene sheet.
The beam is collimated near the target and between
the sample and the detector at 30-m station.
A third collimator is placed before the B-F(3) counter
at the 60-m station. (see Fig.2 of reference).
Impurity resonances used for
normalisation, INTEGRAL(SIGMA-FISSION(E)*DE) on the
resonances at 203.46 eV, 203.93 eV and 195.36 eV
equalised to the values given by H.Derrien et al,
1966 Paris Conf. vol.II, p.195.
Placed within the inner cylinder of the
detector, screened by 1 cm lead, 5 discs in aluminium
canning, diameter = 7.620+-0.013 cm,
containing 54.3347 gr 94-Pu-240 metal
alloyed with 1.2 %  aluminium.
